definitions.definition: ( nautical ) A pontoon ; a narrow shallow boat propelled by a pole .

definitions.definition: ( rugby , American football , soccer ) A kick made by a player who drops the ball and kicks it before it hits the ground.

definitions.definition: A point in the game of faro .
The act of playing at basset , baccara , faro , etc.

examples: Anyone up for a punt on Randwick?

definitions.definition: ( Australia ) Gambling , as a pastime , especially betting on horseraces or the dogs .
A highly speculative investment or other commitment.
An indentation in the base of a wine bottle .
( glassblowing ) A thin glass rod which is temporarily attached to a larger piece in order to better manipulate the larger piece.
